<br>
Dar</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#212141><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uniliz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>niliz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3:51:22 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Zoning times</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My experience with a recent upgrade to my own PC concerning zoning times is that it's basically a memory issue. Expanding memory from 128M to 384M cut down zoning times (which were very high on HD activity, mainly for virtual memory) from 60 sec to a 10-15 sec average, with hardly any disk activity. So if you want fast zoning times, go for more memory than 128M.<br>
<br>
Another note: with 128M I've experienced occasional EQ crashes when going link dead (either being dropped by the server or my local link went down). With 384M this problem never happened anymore (and yes, still went LD a lot, cuz my links sucks).<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
<br>
Niliz Ambrai.<br>
Thirty-something rogue of Caer Cadarn.</font><P>---<BR>

